The paper deals with the complexity of manipulating the Deferred Acceptance Algorithm (DAA) in two-sided matching markets. This falls under the category of Game Theory (cs.GT) as it involves analyzing the strategic behavior of agents. The paper also presents efficient algorithms to compute a manipulation, which involves computational aspects and falls under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Learning (cs.LG). The experiments conducted to analyze the frequency of manipulable instances involve data analysis and statistics, which fall under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
